.Dd March 11, 2026
.Dt MONBSD 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm monbsd
.Nd system monitor for FreeBSD laptops
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a lightweight terminal-based system monitor specifically designed for FreeBSD laptops.
It provides granular monitoring of system health, focusing on thermal performance,
power management, and hardware status.
.Pp
The following information is displayed:
.Bl -bullet -offset indent
.It
System uptime, load average, and CPU model.
.It
Real-time CPU and GPU temperatures.
.It
CPU frequency and core usage.
.It
Memory and swap usage.
.It
Network interface RX/TX rates.
.It
Disk usage for common mount points.
.It
ACPI states, battery status, and fan speed (where supported).
.It
Counts of installed packages and ports.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/dev/cpuctl0" -compact
.It Pa /dev/cpuctl*
Used for direct MSR access to read CPU temperature and performance counters.
.It Pa /dev/io
Used for direct PCI configuration space access.
.El
.Sh PRIVILEGES
.Nm
requires access to
.Pa /dev/cpuctl0
and
.Pa /dev/io .
It is typically installed with setuid root or must be run via
.Xr sudo 8 .
.Sh INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
The following keys can be used while
.Nm
is running:
.Bl -tag -width "q, Q, Ctrl+C" -compact
.It Ic q, Q, Ctrl+C
Exit the program.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr sysctl 8 ,
.Xr pciconf 8 ,
.Xr pkg 8 ,
.Xr powerd 8
.Sh AUTHORS
.An orpheus497
